===Pronunciation===
* {{AHD|pī}}, {{IPA|/paɪ/}}, {{SAMPA|/paI/}}
* {{audio|en-us-pie.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* Homophones: [[pi]], [[π]]
* {{rhymes|aɪ}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|s|-}}

# A type of [[pastry]] that consists of an outer crust and a [[filling]].
#: ''The family had steak and kidney '''pie''' for dinner and cherry '''pie''' for dessert.''
# Extended to other, non-pastry dishes that maintain the general concept of a shell with a filling.
#: ''Shepherd's '''pie''' is made of mince covered with mashed potato.''
# {{context|Northeastern US}} [[pizza|Pizza]].
# {{context|printing}} A disorderly mess of spilt [[type]].
# {{context|cricket}} An especially badly [[bowl]]ed ball.

